WEBVTT

00:01.168 --> 00:03.535
<i> Previously on</i> Queen Sugar...

00:03.570 --> 00:05.937
I got memories
that I'd left in the past

00:05.972 --> 00:07.739
seeping into my bones again.

00:07.774 --> 00:10.308
You're just insecure,
lying trash who'll never

00:10.343 --> 00:13.645
be more than what she's
always been, irrelevant.

00:13.680 --> 00:15.047
I can get at the real story.

00:15.082 --> 00:16.815
You don't have to do
all this on your own.

00:16.850 --> 00:18.617
My past led me to you,

00:18.652 --> 00:21.920
and that led me to want
to be a better man.

00:21.955 --> 00:23.822
One minute, you were
downing jello shots

00:23.857 --> 00:25.524
before he dragged you
upstairs.

00:25.559 --> 00:28.493
Don't no man have
the right to take
advantage of you.

00:28.528 --> 00:30.062
<i> No means no.</i>

00:31.364 --> 00:33.231
-Am I doing this right?
-[Charley] Come on, smile.

00:33.266 --> 00:35.367
-[camera beeps]
-Mom, be careful
with that thing.

00:35.402 --> 00:37.235
I got the settings
just how I like it.

00:37.270 --> 00:39.071
Hush. I'm doing this.

00:39.106 --> 00:41.773
[Hollywood] Charley,
don't be messing with
the boy's camera.

00:41.808 --> 00:44.543
-Ma, you're not even
holding it right.
-Okay, all right. Fine, fine.

00:44.578 --> 00:46.945
[Hollywood] A young Prince
and Nona Gaye. All right, now.

00:46.980 --> 00:48.614
-[laughter and chattering]
- Who?

00:50.050 --> 00:52.551
I poured sparkling cider so we
can all toast this gorgeous,

00:52.586 --> 00:55.320
smart couple
before they head out.

00:57.457 --> 00:59.524
We celebrate this young queen
and king today,

00:59.559 --> 01:03.028
not only for their beauty,
but also for their brains.

01:03.063 --> 01:05.130
Round of applause
to Keke,

01:05.165 --> 01:07.132
who's going
to my Tulane University,

01:07.167 --> 01:08.500
on a full
visual arts scholarship!

01:08.535 --> 01:10.168
-[all cheer]
-That's right.

01:10.203 --> 01:11.603
Go, Green Wave.

01:11.638 --> 01:12.804
[laughs]

01:12.839 --> 01:14.506
And our dear Micah West,

01:14.541 --> 01:17.375
who's taking his talents
all the way across the country

01:17.410 --> 01:20.145
-to...
-[all] Harvard.

01:20.180 --> 01:23.048
My baby's going
to Harvard.

01:23.083 --> 01:24.483
[Hollywood]
All right, now.

01:24.518 --> 01:26.351
Gonna be like my man,
um, who's always looking

01:26.386 --> 01:28.353
for people's roots
and family trees on TV.

01:28.388 --> 01:29.955
The next Henry Louis Gates.
Yes.

01:29.990 --> 01:32.724
Yeah, well, I think
we've had enough
roots-finding

01:32.759 --> 01:36.027
and done dodged enough trees
to fill a whole forest.

01:36.062 --> 01:37.863
[laughter]

01:37.898 --> 01:39.264
Thank you, Uncle Hollywood.

01:39.299 --> 01:41.233
-Cheers.
-Thank you, Auntie Nova.

01:41.268 --> 01:42.901
[all]
Cheers.

01:42.936 --> 01:45.203
All right, well, we took
enough photos at Keke's house.

01:45.238 --> 01:46.872
Can we go? Yeah?
We're gonna be late.

01:46.907 --> 01:49.207
For which part?
The pre-prom, the prom,

01:49.242 --> 01:51.076
the post-prom,
the prom proposal,

01:51.111 --> 01:52.310
the prom entrances?

01:52.345 --> 01:53.712
I mean,
it's just so much.

01:53.747 --> 01:55.847
Nah, we're just gonna
keep it simple.

01:55.882 --> 01:57.782
We're just linking
with some friends
before we go to the prom.

01:57.817 --> 01:59.818
Couple of us put in
for a hotel suite, so...

01:59.853 --> 02:02.521
Okay, well, ordinarily,
I would say be home by 11:00,

02:02.556 --> 02:06.458
but tonight I'm just
gonna say have a good time.

02:06.493 --> 02:07.559
Thank you.

02:08.995 --> 02:11.596
Here, let me get
in there right quick.
Let me get in there.

02:11.631 --> 02:12.464
Flower.

02:12.499 --> 02:14.099
Prom party
at the hotel, huh?

02:14.134 --> 02:16.168
-[chuckles]
-I remember them days.

02:16.203 --> 02:19.137
Now, all I'm gonna
tell you, brother,
is just be responsible.

02:19.172 --> 02:20.639
-Okay, young blood?
-Yeah, I hear you.

02:20.674 --> 02:23.141
-I hear you. I promise.
-All right.

02:23.176 --> 02:24.543
[Charley]
Hey, here you go.

02:24.578 --> 02:26.111
-Just in case.
-It's fine, Mom.

02:26.146 --> 02:27.412
-Just in case.
-No.

02:27.447 --> 02:29.014
The forecast said
light showers at most.

02:29.049 --> 02:31.183
Plus, we're gonna be inside
most of the night.

02:31.218 --> 02:32.617
Okay.

02:32.652 --> 02:34.352
-I'm good.
-Okay. Have fun.

02:34.387 --> 02:35.887
-Have fun.
-[Micah] Thank you.

02:35.922 --> 02:38.156
-Shall we?
-We shall.

02:38.191 --> 02:40.392
[Vi] Y'all have
a good time.

02:40.427 --> 02:42.694
All right. Bye, Auntie.

02:42.729 --> 02:44.696
[Charley] Turn around,
and give a little wave.

02:44.731 --> 02:46.331
Just over the shoulder.
Just a little wave.

02:46.366 --> 02:47.899
-Gosh.
-Just do it!

02:47.934 --> 02:49.467
[Hollywood] Looking like
a young El DeBarge over there.

02:49.502 --> 02:51.837
-[all laugh]
-Oh, Lord.

02:55.075 --> 02:56.575
<i> ¶ Dreams never die ¶</i>

02:56.610 --> 02:59.110
<i> ¶ Take flight</i>
<i> As the world turns ¶</i>

02:59.145 --> 03:00.579
<i> ¶ Dreams never die ¶</i>

03:00.614 --> 03:02.347
<i> ¶ Take flight</i>
<i> As the world turns ¶</i>

03:02.382 --> 03:04.516
<i> ¶ Keep the colors</i>
<i> In the lines ¶</i>

03:04.551 --> 03:05.884
<i> ¶ Take flight ¶</i>

03:07.120 --> 03:08.453
<i> ¶ Dreams never die ¶</i>

03:14.427 --> 03:17.496
<i> ¶ Keep the colors</i>
<i> In the lines ¶</i>

03:18.865 --> 03:21.633
<i> ¶ Keep the colors</i>
<i> In the lines, take flight ¶</i>

03:22.369 --> 03:25.470
I remember
when Micah was a baby,

03:25.505 --> 03:27.772
just holding him
on my shoulder.

03:27.807 --> 03:29.774
He was so tiny.

03:29.809 --> 03:31.610
And now look at him.

03:31.645 --> 03:33.445
He's almost a grown man.

03:33.480 --> 03:36.147
Mm-hmm. You worried about what
he might be doing with Keke.

03:36.182 --> 03:38.550
No, I am not worried
about that.

03:38.585 --> 03:42.420
I raised him to do
the right thing.

03:42.455 --> 03:44.589
And I plan to keep myself
very busy

03:44.624 --> 03:47.392
not worrying about it
with this town hall

03:47.427 --> 03:48.693
to prepare for.

03:48.728 --> 03:50.462
-Sounds like a good plan.
-I just--

03:50.497 --> 03:51.830
I need to be
ready for anything

03:51.865 --> 03:54.466
the Landry-Boudreauxs
throw my way.

03:54.501 --> 03:56.901
The polls have tightened.
I can't take any chances.

03:56.936 --> 04:01.273
Oh, hey, well, the diner
is ready for your walk-through.

04:01.308 --> 04:04.109
You've got the key. If you need
anything, you just call me.

04:04.144 --> 04:06.011
-Thanks, Aunt Vi.
-[Vi] You're welcome, baby.

04:17.457 --> 04:20.759
I know you're worried
about the polls.

04:20.794 --> 04:23.228
I didn't want to share this
when we weren't speaking,

04:23.263 --> 04:25.263
but now...

04:25.298 --> 04:26.798
What is it?

04:26.833 --> 04:28.667
I learned something
on my book tour

04:28.702 --> 04:30.368
that I think you should know.

04:30.403 --> 04:32.604
I figured it's something
you could use at the debate

04:32.639 --> 04:35.040
to keep Jacob
off balance.

04:35.075 --> 04:39.044
Just in case you need more...
ammunition.

04:45.452 --> 04:46.685
[Deesha]
Cold and freshly made.

04:46.720 --> 04:48.953
Ah. Thank you.
Appreciate it.

04:48.988 --> 04:50.989
And you, of course.

04:51.024 --> 04:53.391
[children laughing]

04:53.426 --> 04:55.727
-Joie!
-Whoa! Ahh. Whoa, now.

04:55.762 --> 04:57.662
Joie Sonnier,
where are your manners?

04:57.697 --> 05:00.598
You didn't even speak
to Mr. Bordelon when he came in.

05:00.633 --> 05:02.734
Hello, Mr. Ralph Angel.

05:02.769 --> 05:04.202
And?

05:04.237 --> 05:05.670
-And thanks.
-Mm-mm.

05:05.705 --> 05:07.372
Thank you
for bringing Blue over.

05:07.407 --> 05:09.541
You are very welcome,
Miss Joie.

05:09.576 --> 05:12.444
Joie, you have to see
the spaceship Pops got.

05:12.479 --> 05:15.513
It has flames painted
on the wings and everything.

05:15.548 --> 05:16.982
Oh, it's right there.

05:21.187 --> 05:24.622
I can't tell you how sorry I am
for missing our last date.

05:24.657 --> 05:26.591
I should have
just been real with you

05:26.626 --> 05:28.360
about what's going on.

05:29.863 --> 05:31.463
Things happen.

05:34.067 --> 05:36.134
But is everything okay?

05:36.169 --> 05:40.205
I mean, it took a playdate with
our kids for me to even see you.

05:40.240 --> 05:42.474
Is there anything
I need to know?

05:43.510 --> 05:46.578
It's just kind of complicated.

05:47.814 --> 05:49.047
Well...

05:51.618 --> 05:55.820
Better get some snacks
before these kids get too antsy.

05:55.855 --> 05:57.989
-[thunder rumbling]
-[sighs]

05:58.958 --> 06:01.026
[Nova]
Try that last bit again.

06:02.429 --> 06:04.796
"My goal in running
for city council

06:04.831 --> 06:08.400
is to continue
to build a community

06:08.435 --> 06:09.934
that's better
for all of us.

06:09.969 --> 06:13.104
Just as St. Jo has made me
a better person,

06:13.139 --> 06:15.173
I hope to give back--"

06:15.208 --> 06:16.975
Don't forget the people
in the side booths.

06:17.010 --> 06:18.176
Oh, right. Uh...

06:18.211 --> 06:19.878
"I welcome...

06:19.913 --> 06:23.047
I-I-I welcome
this opportunity today

06:23.082 --> 06:24.849
to help you get to know me

06:24.884 --> 06:28.720
and how we can use Prop K
to stop the incoming highway

06:28.755 --> 06:30.488
and fracking industry--"

06:30.523 --> 06:32.590
Miss Bordelon,
Jacob Boudreaux was born here,

06:32.625 --> 06:34.726
raised here.
Why should we trust you?

06:34.761 --> 06:37.629
A carpetbagger basketball wife
from Tinseltown?

06:37.664 --> 06:40.031
Wait. What? I'm not--

06:40.066 --> 06:42.100
I know, but if Jacob
throws you off like that

06:42.135 --> 06:44.602
or if you feel like
you're losing the crowd
or the local press,

06:44.637 --> 06:47.272
then you have got to change
the power dynamic.

06:47.307 --> 06:48.873
Turnabout is fair play here.

06:48.908 --> 06:51.109
-Throw him off his game.
-Control the narrative.

06:51.144 --> 06:54.646
Of course.
He's going to attack my past.

06:54.681 --> 06:56.881
My life is an open book now,
right?

06:56.916 --> 07:00.318
But theirs isn't.
Not yet.

07:00.353 --> 07:03.955
This would be the time to use
the info from the lineages book.

07:03.990 --> 07:06.891
It's completely unexpected,
puts them on the defensive,

07:06.926 --> 07:10.395
and shifts the narrative
back in your control.

07:10.430 --> 07:13.165
Are you even sure
that it's accurate?

07:14.400 --> 07:16.668
I mean, it's a lot.

07:16.703 --> 07:19.604
It is, but I went
back to the show

07:19.639 --> 07:21.606
to see the evidence
for myself.

07:21.641 --> 07:23.708
It's legit.

07:23.743 --> 07:25.677
[cell phone buzzes]

07:30.049 --> 07:32.851
Oh, that smile tells me
you just got good news.

07:32.886 --> 07:33.852
Calvin.

07:33.887 --> 07:35.687
He's coming for my birthday.

07:35.722 --> 07:38.656
Belated,
but he's coming anyway.

07:38.691 --> 07:41.192
Well, better late
than never.

07:41.227 --> 07:42.393
Go.

07:42.428 --> 07:44.662
Get home, and freshen up.

07:44.697 --> 07:46.998
You know,
light some incense.

07:47.033 --> 07:49.033
-Change the sheets.
-Stop!

07:49.068 --> 07:51.436
-Let's just keep--
-Nova, you're blushing.

07:51.471 --> 07:52.837
-Get out of here.
-[laughs]

07:52.872 --> 07:54.405
You're not going
to be able to focus,

07:54.440 --> 07:58.309
and I'll be better on my own
practicing, anyway.

07:58.344 --> 07:59.678
Go.

08:02.081 --> 08:04.015
-[both laugh]
-Girl, get it.

08:05.785 --> 08:07.852
Don't hurt him.

08:07.887 --> 08:10.055
-Oh, he can handle it.
-[laughs]

08:12.492 --> 08:15.894
[door opens and closes]

08:20.300 --> 08:23.334
[sultry music playing]

08:23.369 --> 08:25.203
<i> ¶ Pass it on ¶</i>

08:27.240 --> 08:30.642
<i> ¶ Goes back</i>
<i> Way before my time ¶</i>

08:30.677 --> 08:32.911
<i> ¶ Thinking on ¶</i>

08:34.447 --> 08:37.215
<i>-¶ How you never left my side ¶</i>
-[knock on door]

08:42.388 --> 08:43.821
[giggles]

08:43.856 --> 08:45.190
Happy belated birthday.

08:46.459 --> 08:50.328
¶ Happy birthday, sweet Nova ¶

08:50.363 --> 08:55.066
¶ Happy birthday to you ¶

08:55.101 --> 08:56.268
[laughs]

09:03.242 --> 09:05.844
I made a reservation
at your favorite restaurant.

09:06.713 --> 09:08.079
And, of course,

09:08.114 --> 09:09.981
I came bearing gifts.

09:15.188 --> 09:16.955
It's beautiful.

09:16.990 --> 09:19.090
-It's the first of many.
-Thank you.

09:19.125 --> 09:20.625
[laughs]

09:20.660 --> 09:22.928
-May I?
-Mm-hmm.

09:29.469 --> 09:31.202
Hey. No peeking.

09:31.237 --> 09:32.571
[laughs]

09:33.473 --> 09:34.873
Okay.

09:41.481 --> 09:43.281
Now that's a start.

09:43.316 --> 09:45.583
-[thunder rumbling]
-One Mississippi.

09:45.618 --> 09:47.953
Two Mississippi.

09:49.088 --> 09:50.888
Storm is about a mile away.

09:50.923 --> 09:52.390
Well, if it's that close,

09:52.425 --> 09:54.592
my favorite restaurant
is right here at home.

09:54.627 --> 09:56.260
I'll cook.

09:56.295 --> 09:58.863
No, I'll cook.

09:58.898 --> 10:00.531
Well, come on, then.

10:00.566 --> 10:01.733
Do your thing.

10:01.768 --> 10:03.267
-[laughs]
-[smacks]

10:03.302 --> 10:04.268
Oh!

10:04.303 --> 10:05.403
I mean, you know...

10:05.438 --> 10:07.172
[knock on door]

10:08.241 --> 10:10.074
[all]
Hey!

10:10.109 --> 10:12.076
[excited chatter]

10:12.111 --> 10:13.611
Bro. Bro.

10:13.646 --> 10:14.879
You don't have
to do it like that.

10:14.914 --> 10:16.481
I have to step out
one time, bro.

10:16.516 --> 10:18.683
It's prom, man.
Good to see you.

10:20.286 --> 10:22.087
[indistinct chatter]

10:23.756 --> 10:26.290
-He wasn't ready.
-They weren't ready.

10:26.325 --> 10:28.426
-What's good, Miss Asha?
-Micah, what's good, man?

10:28.461 --> 10:29.794
Yo, what happened to Ant?

10:29.829 --> 10:31.963
I thought he was gonna
ride over with you guys.

10:31.998 --> 10:34.165
Yeah, he called last minute
saying he wasn't really
like, feeling well,

10:34.200 --> 10:36.701
-so he was gonna pass.
-Man.

10:36.736 --> 10:37.869
You know, he probably
didn't feel comfortable

10:37.904 --> 10:39.070
being around
a bunch of people.

10:39.105 --> 10:40.571
We just got to,
you know,

10:40.606 --> 10:42.040
-give him time.
-Right.

10:42.075 --> 10:45.043
Well, I suggest
we raise a toast.

10:45.078 --> 10:47.578
All right, y'all, to Ant.

10:47.613 --> 10:50.648
-And to his future.
-[all] To Ant.

10:50.683 --> 10:52.817
Oof. Mm.

10:52.852 --> 10:54.352
Okay, I definitely
didn't need...

10:54.387 --> 10:56.354
-That's something.
-We should hold up on that

10:56.389 --> 10:57.655
until the after-party.

10:57.690 --> 10:59.557
We at least want
to walk into prom sober.

10:59.592 --> 11:00.858
What's the fun of that?

11:00.893 --> 11:02.894
So speaking
of the after-party...

11:02.929 --> 11:04.996
so there was a little mix-up
when I went to check in.

11:05.031 --> 11:07.598
You know, Micah, Malik.
Malik, Micah.

11:07.633 --> 11:09.300
Now, I'm not saying who,

11:09.335 --> 11:11.335
but it seems like
somebody in this room

11:11.370 --> 11:13.971
booked themselves a private room
down the hall.

11:14.006 --> 11:15.773
I'm assuming for later.

11:15.808 --> 11:17.675
-No, that's not--
-[boys laugh]

11:17.710 --> 11:19.010
No, I just got that one

11:19.045 --> 11:20.778
just in case we couldn't
get this one.

11:20.813 --> 11:22.947
-Yeah, okay. Right.
-[Micah] Shut up, man.

11:22.982 --> 11:25.049
Davis West's name cuts through
a lot of red tape.

11:25.084 --> 11:27.552
-Red tape? I get you.
-Red tape? Red tape.

11:27.587 --> 11:29.087
My fault, yeah.

11:29.122 --> 11:30.688
I just forgot to cancel it.

11:30.723 --> 11:32.056
-[indistinct chatter]
-[thunder rumbling]

11:32.091 --> 11:34.092
-Whatever you say.
-Okay, cool.

11:35.461 --> 11:36.861
Y'all saw that?

11:40.299 --> 11:41.899
Whoa.

11:41.934 --> 11:43.768
[thunder crashing]

11:46.038 --> 11:47.538
-What is going--
-[electricity hums]

11:47.573 --> 11:49.074
Great.

11:52.411 --> 11:56.814
"My opponent would
take our land, build a highway,

11:56.849 --> 11:58.516
and decimate our farms

11:58.551 --> 12:01.786
in order to support
fracking operations

12:01.821 --> 12:04.689
that will only build wealth
for a chosen few.

12:04.724 --> 12:07.358
But together,
we can create a future."

12:07.393 --> 12:09.227
[clapping]

12:10.696 --> 12:13.498
Well done, Charley.

12:14.634 --> 12:17.335
Resorting to spying, Jacob.

12:17.370 --> 12:21.172
Your prep walk-through is
scheduled for tomorrow morning.

12:21.207 --> 12:22.473
This is my time.

12:22.508 --> 12:24.408
I know.

12:24.443 --> 12:26.110
I wanted
to talk to you,

12:26.145 --> 12:28.212
but you've ducked
my calls.

12:28.247 --> 12:31.549
Because I don't want
to talk to you.

12:31.584 --> 12:33.118
We're competitors.

12:33.986 --> 12:36.154
To say we're competitors

12:36.189 --> 12:38.289
would mean either one of us
could win this thing.

12:38.324 --> 12:40.892
But the truth is,

12:40.927 --> 12:43.394
you don't have
a chance to win.

12:43.429 --> 12:45.263
At all.

12:45.298 --> 12:46.431
I'm sorry.

12:48.167 --> 12:50.201
You think you've
got it in the bag?

12:50.236 --> 12:51.736
Charley, I've been told
it's a done deal

12:51.771 --> 12:53.404
and that I've already won.

12:53.439 --> 12:57.809
But I want to urge you
to get out before it's too late.

12:57.844 --> 13:00.178
The arrogance
of mediocre white men

13:00.213 --> 13:02.814
never ceases
to astound me.

13:02.849 --> 13:05.383
It's not arrogance,
Charley.

13:05.418 --> 13:06.751
It's power.

13:06.786 --> 13:08.186
I told you,

13:08.221 --> 13:10.955
my family stops at nothing
that gets in their way.

13:15.661 --> 13:18.496
My mother, for some reason,
is suddenly livid with you.

13:18.531 --> 13:21.465
-I'll bet she is.
-Believe it or not,

13:21.500 --> 13:24.969
everything that's happened
'til now is just business.

13:25.004 --> 13:27.772
But she and the people
she's working with,

13:27.807 --> 13:30.575
they intend to destroy you
and your family...

13:30.610 --> 13:32.243
completely.

13:32.278 --> 13:34.745
Now it's gotten personal.

13:34.780 --> 13:38.049
<i> Now</i> it's gotten
personal?

13:40.519 --> 13:42.253
I've heard enough.

13:42.288 --> 13:46.090
Your attempts at intimidation
are weak,

13:46.125 --> 13:49.894
and I have got better things
to do with my time.

