18:11.924 --> 18:13.224
<i> ¶ If you love me ¶</i>

18:13.259 --> 18:14.592
<i> ¶ Won't you say something? ¶</i>

18:14.627 --> 18:16.060
[knock on door]

18:16.095 --> 18:17.928
<i> -¶ If you love me... ¶</i>
-[thunder rumbling]

18:17.963 --> 18:19.697
[sighs]

18:19.732 --> 18:21.299
Come in.

18:24.303 --> 18:26.604
-How are the roads looking?
-Whoa.

18:26.639 --> 18:28.205
Not good.

18:28.240 --> 18:30.274
[cell phones chime]

18:34.380 --> 18:37.982
"We regret to inform you that
due to flooding at the venue,

18:38.017 --> 18:41.152
"tonight's prom festivities
have been canceled.

18:41.187 --> 18:44.422
Further information
to follow when available."

18:47.560 --> 18:49.793
The kids made a tent
in Joie's room

18:49.828 --> 18:52.163
after it
started to rain.

18:52.198 --> 18:54.331
They'll be be cleaned up
in a minute.

18:54.366 --> 18:56.600
Glad they had a good time.

18:56.635 --> 18:58.803
Appreciate you
looking after him.

19:02.408 --> 19:05.209
Were you able
to stay dry?

19:05.244 --> 19:09.079
Hope you weren't working
in this rain today.

19:09.114 --> 19:10.447
Ah...

19:10.482 --> 19:13.384
I didn't make it back
to the farm today.

19:15.120 --> 19:17.154
There's, um...

19:17.189 --> 19:19.624
something I've been meaning
to tell you.

19:21.760 --> 19:24.462
I ain't been all the way
honest with you, Deesha.

19:27.199 --> 19:30.467
I've been going
to see Darla every day

19:30.502 --> 19:32.703
for the last
two weeks now.

19:34.573 --> 19:35.773
She, uh--

19:36.875 --> 19:38.709
she had a relapse

19:38.744 --> 19:41.546
the night I missed
our date.

19:44.383 --> 19:47.017
Is she going to be okay?

19:47.052 --> 19:49.253
How is Blue doing
with all of this?

19:49.288 --> 19:50.821
Don't even know yet.

19:52.458 --> 19:53.824
She's trying to, you know...

19:55.461 --> 19:59.163
do all the steps
to recover first.

19:59.198 --> 20:04.435
Well, at least she's taking
her recovery seriously.

20:05.804 --> 20:07.705
Yeah. She is.

20:16.048 --> 20:17.481
Look, Deesha...

20:20.085 --> 20:21.652
you're an amazing woman.

20:22.755 --> 20:23.888
I just...

20:25.758 --> 20:26.757
I just wish--

20:26.792 --> 20:28.960
You didn't have
other obligations?

20:30.396 --> 20:34.765
Thing is,
ain't even obligations. I...

20:36.268 --> 20:37.935
I could just see now that...

20:40.139 --> 20:43.340
if she hurtin', I'm hurtin'.

20:43.375 --> 20:46.377
If she bleed, I bleed.

20:50.749 --> 20:54.919
Ain't even sure it's much
of a choice at this point.

20:56.955 --> 20:58.356
But...

20:59.658 --> 21:02.026
I'm still in love
with Darla.

21:19.978 --> 21:23.480
What you just said is one
of the most beautiful things

21:23.515 --> 21:25.816
a man could say to a woman.

21:27.419 --> 21:30.421
But I'm not the woman
you're talking about,

21:30.456 --> 21:36.160
and I respect myself too much
to play second fiddle.

21:36.195 --> 21:37.995
You deserve more than that.

21:38.030 --> 21:40.431
I know I do.

21:41.467 --> 21:44.201
But I wish you well,
Ralph Angel.

21:44.236 --> 21:46.270
[chuckles]

21:46.305 --> 21:47.738
Blue and Darla, too.

21:50.909 --> 21:54.312
We'll work something out
with the kids, okay?

22:03.989 --> 22:05.523
[sighs]

22:11.563 --> 22:12.930
[soft music playing]

22:12.965 --> 22:14.798
[Calvin]
Oh, yes.

22:14.833 --> 22:16.567
<i> ¶ I wanna get closer to you ¶</i>

22:16.602 --> 22:19.436
<i> ¶ I wanna get close... ¶</i>

22:19.471 --> 22:21.638
That smells good.

22:21.673 --> 22:24.041
<i> ¶ I wanna get closer to you ¶</i>

22:24.076 --> 22:27.111
<i> ¶ I wanna</i>
<i> Get closer to you ¶</i>

22:27.146 --> 22:30.648
<i> -¶ I wanna get close to you ¶</i>
-[thunder rumbling]

22:31.717 --> 22:32.983
What?

22:34.119 --> 22:35.486
Look at us.

22:35.521 --> 22:38.021
I mean, we've never
been like this.

22:38.056 --> 22:40.157
Domestic...

22:40.192 --> 22:41.525
together.

22:41.560 --> 22:43.661
Yeah, guess you're right.

22:45.063 --> 22:46.497
We never had the time.

22:48.133 --> 22:49.299
Or the freedom.

22:49.334 --> 22:51.668
This is good.

22:51.703 --> 22:54.371
And that chicken
looks amazing.

22:54.406 --> 22:56.440
You really are
good at this.

22:56.475 --> 22:58.308
And you're
a good sous-chef.

22:58.343 --> 23:01.345
-Oh, I think I'm head chef here.
-Too many cooks, baby.

23:01.380 --> 23:03.680
-Mm-hmm.
-Mm-hmm. Please, sit.

23:03.715 --> 23:06.150
-[laughing]
-I will be doing the serving.

23:13.659 --> 23:15.893
How about we do this
more often?

23:17.262 --> 23:18.696
Like next weekend.

23:20.699 --> 23:23.167
I would love to,
but I have the kids next week.

23:23.202 --> 23:25.369
I'm taking 'em camping.

23:25.404 --> 23:26.937
How 'bout the week after?

23:26.972 --> 23:28.272
Can't.

23:28.307 --> 23:32.476
I'm hosting a writing workshop
back in Atlanta.

23:33.712 --> 23:35.779
And then you've got
the kids again, right?

23:35.814 --> 23:38.148
It's my two-week vacation
with them.

23:38.183 --> 23:40.117
-[cork pops
-[laughs]

23:42.154 --> 23:45.155
So that's four or five weeks

23:45.190 --> 23:47.558
before we see each other again?

23:54.433 --> 23:56.066
Look, Charley,

23:56.101 --> 23:58.202
I know who I am,
where I come from.

23:58.237 --> 24:00.103
I know how I was raised.

24:00.138 --> 24:01.472
Do you?

24:03.842 --> 24:05.543
Really?

24:16.455 --> 24:19.289
[Frances, on recording]
<i> You don't get to</i>
<i> question me, gal.</i>

24:19.324 --> 24:20.958
<i> I do love this land.</i>

24:20.993 --> 24:23.427
<i> What I love most</i>
<i> is that sugar cane.</i>

24:23.462 --> 24:25.128
<i> After it's washed,</i>
<i> processed,</i>

24:25.163 --> 24:27.598
<i> and all the impurities</i>
<i> are squeezed out of it,</i>

24:27.633 --> 24:29.833
<i> it comes forth</i>
<i> as white as snow,</i>

24:29.868 --> 24:31.435
<i> the way it should be.</i>

24:31.470 --> 24:32.736
What...

24:32.771 --> 24:34.438
<i> You needed to be put</i>
<i> in your place.</i>

24:34.473 --> 24:37.474
<i> You're nothing more</i>
<i> than an upstart mulatta gal</i>

24:37.509 --> 24:39.076
<i> pretending to be white.</i>

24:39.111 --> 24:41.345
<i> But I guess</i>
<i> that's your mother's fault.</i>

24:41.380 --> 24:43.214
[thunder rumbles]

24:48.320 --> 24:49.920
That's your mama, Jacob.

24:52.291 --> 24:54.992
Still want to talk
about how you were raised?

25:01.466 --> 25:03.534
You know the difference

25:03.569 --> 25:05.803
between you and me?

25:09.708 --> 25:11.542
I know my shame.

25:13.445 --> 25:16.180
I've dealt
with my issues.

25:18.016 --> 25:19.149
But, Jacob...

25:20.385 --> 25:24.021
despite the evidence
of all of American history...

25:26.592 --> 25:28.025
your history...

25:30.062 --> 25:32.296
you can't even
acknowledge that...

25:34.666 --> 25:38.702
your issues around whiteness
even exist.

25:43.809 --> 25:45.543
How could I be better?

25:50.282 --> 25:52.116
Drop out of the race.

25:53.552 --> 25:55.052
I can't do that.
I want to.

25:55.087 --> 25:56.787
I don't even want
to be a councilman,

25:56.822 --> 25:58.355
but it's too late
for that now.

25:58.390 --> 26:02.059
Wow, so there's-- there's
nothing that you can do?

26:02.094 --> 26:03.961
I can promise to work with you
once I'm in office.

26:03.996 --> 26:06.664
No. No, that is
not good enough.

26:07.532 --> 26:09.266
Do better.

26:11.603 --> 26:14.572
I can't just drop out
of the race.

26:15.874 --> 26:19.209
But maybe I can find a way
to make myself unelectable,

26:19.244 --> 26:21.879
you know, throw the race.

26:26.151 --> 26:28.919
I think I can help you
with that.

26:38.830 --> 26:40.263
What are you doing
with a picture

26:40.298 --> 26:42.733
of my great-grandmother
Landry?

26:47.205 --> 26:48.572
Oh.

26:48.607 --> 26:50.174
God bless the rain.

26:52.177 --> 26:55.145
-Oh, we needed this, baby.
-Mm-hmm.

26:55.180 --> 26:56.980
No diner, no family.

26:57.015 --> 26:58.348
Just us.

26:58.383 --> 27:00.017
Shoot, I don't even remember

27:00.052 --> 27:01.952
the last time
I was this relaxed.

27:01.987 --> 27:03.620
See?

27:03.655 --> 27:06.690
You guys make fun
of us ladies

27:06.725 --> 27:10.060
for going for our spas
and massages.

27:11.797 --> 27:14.264
You need a little bit
of self-care yourself.

27:14.299 --> 27:16.099
You ain't got
to convince me, baby.

27:16.134 --> 27:18.268
It's them other Joes
you talking about.

27:18.303 --> 27:20.971
I wonder if I could
convince them, though.

27:21.006 --> 27:22.673
I been hearing
about these places

27:22.708 --> 27:24.508
popping up
around the country.

27:24.543 --> 27:28.445
Black men just coming together,
sitting around,

27:28.480 --> 27:29.980
talking,

27:30.015 --> 27:32.115
giving each other advice.

27:32.150 --> 27:35.052
Lift each other up
when times get tough.

27:35.087 --> 27:36.586
Now, that's something
I could get down with.

27:36.621 --> 27:38.021
Ah, a support group?

27:38.056 --> 27:39.723
Nah, I can't call it that,
though.

27:39.758 --> 27:41.324
[both laugh]

27:41.359 --> 27:43.026
Thinking about calling it
"The Hangout."

27:43.061 --> 27:46.863
That sounds like a place
where folks get arrested.

27:46.898 --> 27:48.165
-You can do better.
-Okay.

27:48.200 --> 27:49.900
Well, what about--
what about...

27:49.935 --> 27:53.670
the St. Jo's Men's Social Club?

27:53.705 --> 27:56.406
Well, you told me
that I'm the only one

27:56.441 --> 27:59.609
where you feel like you could
talk to about the real stuff.

27:59.644 --> 28:01.178
Right?

28:01.213 --> 28:02.879
Well, if that's what you want
for this place,

28:02.914 --> 28:04.548
well, I don't know,

28:04.583 --> 28:07.884
maybe call it "The Real Stuff."

28:07.919 --> 28:12.422
Well, what about
"The Real Spot"?

28:12.457 --> 28:14.391
There it is. I like that.

28:14.426 --> 28:17.094
-[Hollywood] The Real Spot.
-[Violet] Yeah.

28:20.599 --> 28:22.466
[thunder rumbling]

28:22.501 --> 28:23.667
Thank you.

28:23.702 --> 28:25.168
Hey.

28:25.203 --> 28:28.505
You didn't have to do that
in all this rain.

28:28.540 --> 28:30.340
It's all good.

28:30.375 --> 28:32.676
Just wanted to see
how you getting through today.

28:32.711 --> 28:34.044
Like you did
the day before last

28:34.079 --> 28:36.513
and the day before that.

28:36.548 --> 28:40.184
Got you some chicken soup before
the rain shuts stuff down.

28:41.253 --> 28:43.220
That kind you like
from Poppa Joe's.

28:44.222 --> 28:45.255
Yeah.

28:46.324 --> 28:47.591
How you feeling?

28:47.626 --> 28:49.326
I took some time
off of work.

28:50.829 --> 28:52.195
I called Marlene.

28:52.230 --> 28:56.466
I'm trying to send her
my actions right now

28:56.501 --> 28:59.102
and not my feelings.

28:59.137 --> 29:00.938
That's what's up.

29:02.007 --> 29:04.341
Yeah, that's what's up.

29:05.577 --> 29:06.910
[sighs]

29:08.580 --> 29:11.014
Blue been wondering
about you.

29:12.217 --> 29:13.884
Told him you ain't
been feeling too good

29:13.919 --> 29:16.787
so you went down
to your mama's.

29:21.359 --> 29:23.227
Look, Darla, just...

29:25.263 --> 29:27.397
please don't take too long
before you see him.

29:28.767 --> 29:31.435
I really want
to see him, but, um...

29:34.139 --> 29:37.641
but I just need
a little bit more time

29:37.676 --> 29:41.445
to make sure that I'm in
the right condition to do that.

29:48.720 --> 29:50.921
You know, I was
never really sure

29:50.956 --> 29:53.524
when we were gonna
see each other again.

29:55.060 --> 29:57.494
Didn't bother me
so much then.

29:59.130 --> 30:00.297
[laughs]

30:00.332 --> 30:01.565
But...

30:03.268 --> 30:06.303
to be honest
and tell my radical truth...

30:07.372 --> 30:08.371
that worked for me.

30:08.406 --> 30:10.807
It was painful
to be away from you,

30:10.842 --> 30:13.310
but I convinced myself
it was my choice.

30:13.345 --> 30:19.049
At all times,
I remained in control.

30:19.084 --> 30:21.485
[thunder rumbles]

30:23.121 --> 30:24.955
But I can't say
I was happy.

30:28.293 --> 30:29.893
And now?

30:29.928 --> 30:32.863
One thing about
writing a memoir,

30:32.898 --> 30:36.499
you have to face your fears
if you're gonna be authentic.

30:36.534 --> 30:39.469
I can see now that every
relationship I've ever been in

30:39.504 --> 30:45.308
had a built-in, impenetrable
barrier guarding my heart.

30:45.343 --> 30:49.112
With you, it was your race,

30:49.147 --> 30:52.516
your marriage, your kids...

30:53.618 --> 30:55.252
your job.

30:56.388 --> 30:57.787
And now--

30:57.822 --> 30:59.289
Living in two cities.

31:01.559 --> 31:05.495
Maybe our schedules
are something else.

31:08.566 --> 31:10.934
So you're saying I have
a fear of commitment.

31:10.969 --> 31:12.936
No, I'm saying
you were able to commit

31:12.971 --> 31:14.838
because we had distance.

31:14.873 --> 31:16.273
[scoffs]

31:23.114 --> 31:25.249
What if we didn't
have the distance?

31:27.018 --> 31:29.152
What if we threw caution
out the window?

31:29.187 --> 31:33.023
Maybe our happiness
is on the other side

31:33.058 --> 31:35.292
of what we're
comfortable with.

31:36.995 --> 31:39.263
And out of living
in other people's boxes.

31:42.867 --> 31:44.167
Not even our own.

31:44.202 --> 31:47.671
<i> ¶ Starve my heart of ecstasy ¶</i>

31:47.706 --> 31:49.773
[thunder crashes]

31:49.808 --> 31:54.011
<i> ¶ When you're not</i>
<i> The one in front of me ¶</i>

31:55.880 --> 31:57.814
<i> ¶ So I crave no other ¶</i>

31:57.849 --> 32:01.685
<i> ¶ Said I'm cravin' you ¶</i>

32:04.923 --> 32:07.490
-Okay, Malik, you start.
-[Malik] All right.

32:07.525 --> 32:11.127
Where do I see myself
10, 20 years from now?

32:11.162 --> 32:13.430
Well, by then,
I'll have at least five Grammys.

32:13.465 --> 32:15.899
-[Asha] Five?
-Mm-hmm. Go big, or go home.

32:15.934 --> 32:17.434
That's what I always say.

32:17.469 --> 32:19.235
-Since when?
-[Malik] Since right now.

32:19.270 --> 32:22.973
I'm gonna be
living bicoastal,

32:23.008 --> 32:24.708
producing albums
for all the top artists,

32:24.743 --> 32:28.244
and all just dying
for that Strickland sound, brah.

32:28.279 --> 32:29.779
That Strickland sound.

32:29.814 --> 32:31.114
That actually sounds dope.

32:31.149 --> 32:33.516
-Yeah, it does.
-What about you?

32:33.551 --> 32:36.753
I plan to have a whole chain
of urgent care clinics

32:36.788 --> 32:38.121
all throughout Louisiana,

32:38.156 --> 32:40.156
just offering
low-cost healthcare

32:40.191 --> 32:43.693
to those who can least
afford to pay.

32:43.728 --> 32:45.061
That's awesome, Asha.

32:45.096 --> 32:46.463
And you're gonna do it.

32:46.498 --> 32:47.564
[all]
Yeah.

32:47.599 --> 32:50.100
And the slogan
posted in all my offices

32:50.135 --> 32:52.535
is gonna be,
"Do no harm..."

32:52.570 --> 32:53.937
[all]
"...But take no shit."

32:53.972 --> 32:55.805
Y'all already know.

32:55.840 --> 32:58.408
And when them whack-ass
insurance companies
try to shut you down,

32:58.443 --> 33:00.643
I can defend you
with my law firm.

33:00.678 --> 33:02.946
Oh, so you're finally going
to put that big mouth to--

33:02.981 --> 33:06.349
-I mean, that big voice to use?
-All right, whatever.

33:06.384 --> 33:08.151
Wow.

33:08.186 --> 33:09.386
-Right.
-But, yeah.

33:09.421 --> 33:11.254
I plan to start a bail bond

33:11.289 --> 33:13.289
for all our brothers
and sisters, you know,

33:13.324 --> 33:16.393
the ones locked up
for months or years pretrial

33:16.428 --> 33:18.795
because they can't, what,
come up with a hundred

33:18.830 --> 33:20.263
or a couple thousand dollars?

33:20.298 --> 33:21.765
-[Asha] Yeah.
-Yeah.

33:21.800 --> 33:24.801
Think of it like
an Innocence Project and ACLU

33:24.836 --> 33:27.203
-all wrapped in one.
-[Micah] Wow, I respect that.

33:27.238 --> 33:29.039
[Keke]
Well, in ten years,

33:29.074 --> 33:31.007
I will be flying to New York

33:31.042 --> 33:33.977
to present my latest
art installation

33:34.012 --> 33:36.513
right before I jet off to D.C.

33:36.548 --> 33:39.315
to unveil
my commissioned collection

33:39.350 --> 33:41.384
in the African-American Museum.

33:41.419 --> 33:42.786
Okay.

33:42.821 --> 33:45.355
That's what's up.
That's what's up.

33:45.390 --> 33:47.491
Well, how about you, Micah?

33:52.897 --> 33:54.431
I don't know.

33:56.000 --> 33:58.568
I don't know. I'm...

34:01.439 --> 34:03.973
I mean, I guess I'm...

34:04.008 --> 34:06.676
liking my photography
more and more.

34:07.745 --> 34:10.313
I hear a "but" coming.

34:10.348 --> 34:12.783
-But, uh...
-There you go.

34:14.419 --> 34:16.719
I don't know. I feel like,
when it's all said and done,

34:16.754 --> 34:18.788
I'll be doing
something respectable,

34:18.823 --> 34:23.326
like investment banking
or hedge funds.

34:23.361 --> 34:25.395
-Hmm.
-All right.

34:28.333 --> 34:31.101
I've made up my mind
about something,

34:31.136 --> 34:33.303
and I hope
you like it.

34:35.073 --> 34:37.640
Now I'm curious.

34:37.675 --> 34:38.809
What is it?

34:39.611 --> 34:41.545
I'm moving back
to New Orleans.

34:42.814 --> 34:45.548
I would much rather commute
to work in Baton Rouge,

34:45.583 --> 34:47.851
if that allows us
to have something real.

34:50.221 --> 34:53.756
I don't want any more
strange looks from your family,

34:53.791 --> 34:56.126
whether or not
I'm that married cop

34:56.161 --> 34:57.661
who played around
on his wife.

34:59.797 --> 35:02.332
That guy in your book,
I'm not that guy.

35:06.738 --> 35:08.538
Sounds nice.

35:10.008 --> 35:11.708
Like a dream.

35:11.743 --> 35:14.177
It could be real.

35:16.080 --> 35:17.514
Say yes.

35:17.549 --> 35:18.815
To what?

35:18.850 --> 35:20.450
To us.

35:22.554 --> 35:24.354
To happiness.

35:39.504 --> 35:41.304
This soup hitting,
ain't it?

35:41.339 --> 35:43.206
And it's the perfect day
for it.

35:43.241 --> 35:45.074
Mm-hmm.

35:45.109 --> 35:46.309
[sighs]

35:46.344 --> 35:48.044
Thank you, Ralph Angel,

35:48.079 --> 35:49.880
for keeping me company.

35:51.449 --> 35:53.316
I know you didn't have to.

36:07.765 --> 36:09.299
It's all good.

36:11.002 --> 36:12.669
[sighs]

36:15.006 --> 36:16.940
[thunder crashing]

36:29.287 --> 36:31.788
You don't owe me
anything.

36:31.823 --> 36:33.723
I know that.

36:33.758 --> 36:35.792
But I...

36:35.827 --> 36:37.727
I would like to know...

36:39.230 --> 36:41.198
why do you keep coming?

36:43.901 --> 36:45.501
Just 'cause
we ain't together

36:45.536 --> 36:48.638
don't mean I don't care
about you no more.

36:51.776 --> 36:52.976
I have to.

36:55.246 --> 36:57.380
For my own peace of mind,
really.

36:58.483 --> 36:59.950
What do you mean?

37:02.987 --> 37:05.322
All I could think about...

37:09.060 --> 37:11.995
is them
two piece-of-shit bastards

37:12.030 --> 37:13.863
that hurt you.

37:13.898 --> 37:16.233
Ain't nobody
was there for you then.

37:17.368 --> 37:20.036
I don't ever
want you to feel like

37:20.071 --> 37:22.239
nobody's there for you again.

37:23.174 --> 37:24.941
Keep it a hundred,

37:24.976 --> 37:26.443
relapsing...

37:27.779 --> 37:30.580
man, it scared the hell
out of me, Darla,

37:30.615 --> 37:31.848
a lot.

37:33.384 --> 37:35.452
For Blue. Yeah.

37:38.856 --> 37:40.290
For me, too.

37:41.292 --> 37:42.626
[sighs]

37:44.529 --> 37:46.529
It scared me, too.

37:46.564 --> 37:49.399
I ain't felt like that since...

37:49.434 --> 37:51.868
since we first
got together...

37:54.405 --> 37:55.905
before we had Blue.

37:57.642 --> 38:02.445
Man, I spent so much time
just worrying about you.

38:02.480 --> 38:05.281
"Did she make it
in her dorm okay?"

38:05.316 --> 38:07.684
"Hope she had
a good breakfast."

38:09.454 --> 38:11.421
Stupid stuff like that.

38:13.091 --> 38:15.091
It's not stupid.

38:15.126 --> 38:16.593
It's sweet.

38:17.795 --> 38:20.296
Thing is,

38:20.331 --> 38:21.665
nobody tell you...

38:22.867 --> 38:27.437
that loving somebody
could hurt so much.

38:27.472 --> 38:30.740
Always terrified

38:30.775 --> 38:33.443
of losing all the things
you prayed for.

38:35.980 --> 38:37.847
I prayed for you.

38:38.916 --> 38:40.483
I still do.

38:43.321 --> 38:44.754
I pray that...

38:46.157 --> 38:48.291
you could forgive me
one day.

38:48.326 --> 38:50.493
I already told you, I do.

38:51.863 --> 38:53.996
I mean it.

38:54.031 --> 38:55.398
I mean...

38:56.267 --> 38:58.401
really forgive me.

38:59.537 --> 39:01.971
-Forgive me enough to go back...
-[sighs]

39:04.242 --> 39:06.343
to what we had before.

39:20.925 --> 39:23.893
Think you could
ever think about...

39:25.930 --> 39:27.497
us again?

39:29.767 --> 39:31.768
I always do.

39:33.538 --> 39:36.072
I don't think
I never really stopped.

39:39.877 --> 39:41.878
Thanks again for that info.

39:41.913 --> 39:46.182
I think it's going to work in
ways we couldn't have imagined.

39:46.217 --> 39:47.383
Turn on the news.

39:47.418 --> 39:49.385
[types]

39:49.420 --> 39:52.922
<i> It's come to my attention</i>
<i> that Landry Enterprises</i>

39:52.957 --> 39:55.792
<i> has a biased pricing structure</i>
<i> based on race.</i>

39:55.827 --> 39:57.527
<i> That is unacceptable to me.</i>

39:57.562 --> 40:01.230
<i> In order to be a better</i>
<i> candidate for all of St. Jo,</i>

40:01.265 --> 40:02.899
<i> I know I must own</i>
<i> my responsibility</i>

40:02.934 --> 40:05.101
<i> in how things have been done.</i>

40:05.136 --> 40:07.303
<i> That is why I pulled out</i>
<i> of tonight's town hall</i>

40:07.338 --> 40:10.239
<i> and instead have ordered</i>
<i> an immediate audit</i>

40:10.274 --> 40:12.408
<i> to overhaul</i>
<i> the pricing structure</i>

40:12.443 --> 40:14.110
<i> at Landry Enterprises.</i>

40:14.145 --> 40:17.413
<i> Enough talk.</i>
<i> It's time for action.</i>

40:17.448 --> 40:18.815
What is th--

40:18.850 --> 40:20.049
Wait for it.

40:20.084 --> 40:21.584
<i> Recently I have</i>
<i> received information</i>

40:21.619 --> 40:24.253
<i> that has impacted me</i>
<i> to my core.</i>

40:24.288 --> 40:26.422
<i> I share it with you today,</i>

40:26.457 --> 40:28.724
<i> because I believe</i>
<i> all of us in St. Jo</i>

40:28.759 --> 40:31.394
<i> should see each other</i>
<i> as one big family.</i>

40:31.429 --> 40:33.896
<i> I have learned</i>
<i> my great-grandmother Landry</i>

40:33.931 --> 40:36.632
<i> was a proud</i>
<i> African-American woman.</i>

40:36.667 --> 40:38.935
<i> She was, in fact,</i>

40:38.970 --> 40:41.404
<i> secretly a member</i>
<i> of the Bordelon family.</i>

40:41.439 --> 40:45.875
<i> I never expected this,</i>
<i> but I wish to say publicly,</i>

40:45.910 --> 40:49.278
<i> I embrace the diversity</i>
<i> of my heritage.</i>

40:49.313 --> 40:53.583
<i> Going forward,</i>
<i> my goal is to educate myself</i>

40:53.618 --> 40:55.251
<i> on the histories</i>
<i> between our communities</i>

40:55.286 --> 40:57.854
<i> and use that knowledge</i>
<i> to be an ally</i>

40:57.889 --> 41:01.324
<i> and support real change</i>
<i> in St. Jo.</i>

41:01.359 --> 41:02.758
<i> Thank you.</i>

41:02.793 --> 41:04.527
[Nova]<i> Now,</i>
<i> that's a bold move,</i>

41:04.562 --> 41:06.662
but this won't
win him more votes?

41:06.697 --> 41:09.265
If we play this right,
he'll lose 10%,

41:09.300 --> 41:12.034
maybe 15% of his white voters,

41:12.069 --> 41:13.936
the ones who are
blatantly racist.

41:13.971 --> 41:17.707
<i> And the small percentage</i>
<i> of black supporters he has</i>

41:17.742 --> 41:19.709
will reconsider their support
once they start to feel

41:19.744 --> 41:23.613
he's pandering
his newfound ethnicity.

41:23.648 --> 41:25.414
<i> And that should be enough</i>

41:25.449 --> 41:27.550
to tip the race
in my favor.

41:27.585 --> 41:29.452
It's bold, Charley,

41:29.487 --> 41:30.753
Risky,

41:30.788 --> 41:32.855
<i> for you and Jacob.</i>

41:32.890 --> 41:34.891
The Landrys,
the Boudreauxs,

41:34.926 --> 41:36.792
and whomever else they're
working with behind the scenes,

41:36.827 --> 41:40.497
I don't think they handle losing
very well.

41:41.299 --> 41:43.065
Yeah, well...

41:43.100 --> 41:44.734
neither do I.

42:24.875 --> 42:26.943
[woman]
<i> Go, Ree-Ree.</i>
